==English==
===Adverb phrase===
'''per se'''

#By itself; without consideration of extraneous factors

====Usage Note====
Because this is a Latin phrase, it is usually italicized when written.

===Etymology===
Latin '''per se''', by itself, from ''[[per]]'', by or through, and ''[[se]]'', itself, himself, herself or themselves.

